flowchart TD
    A[CLI parses case-study YAML and strict attempt budget] --> B[Construct TGMCTSElitesGenerator]
    B --> C[Load case study with Aerialist]
    C --> D[Resolve referenced QGroundControl plan]
    D --> E[Convert geographic waypoints to local coordinates]
    E --> F[Infer simulator axis/sign mapping from legal-area overlap]
    F --> G[Create or resume mission-aware run directory]
    G --> H[Restore results, confirmations, history, and pending candidate]
    H --> I[Reserve part of sufficiently large budget for confirmation]
    I --> J{Exploration limit reached?}

    J -- No --> K[MCTS select or expand]
    K --> L[Generate or mutate mission-guided obstacle scenario]
    L --> M{Pre-execution validation passes?}
    M -- No --> N[Log invalid candidate without consuming budget]
    N --> J
    M -- Yes --> O[Persist pending candidate]
    O --> P[Consume one simulator-attempt unit]
    P --> Q[Execute Aerialist/PX4]
    Q --> R{Infrastructure or execution result?}

    R -- System error --> S{Retry allowed and budget remains?}
    S -- Yes --> O
    S -- No --> J

    R -- Evaluated --> U[Extract trajectory, minimum distance, and mission outcome]
    U --> V[Compute official point, reward, failure_evidence, and MAP-Elites cell]
    V --> W{Official distance failure and input compliant?}
    W -- Yes --> X[Save YAML, ULG, overview plot, and XY-time plot]
    W -- No --> Y[Keep metadata only and delete temporary heavy files]
    X --> Z[Append result metadata]
    Y --> Z
    Z --> AA[Update MAP-Elites and backpropagate reward]
    AA --> AB[Append history and periodically save tree/progress plots]
    AB --> J

    J -- Yes --> AC{Confirmation reserve available and failures found?}
    AC -- Yes --> AD[Rerun leading completed or non-completed proximity failures]
    AD --> AE{Confirmation reproduces official distance failure?}
    AE -- Yes --> AF[Save separate confirmation failure artifacts]
    AE -- No --> AG[Keep confirmation metadata only]
    AF --> AH[Update point, distance, runtime, and reproducibility samples]
    AG --> AH
    AH --> AI{Unused total budget remains?}
    AI -- Yes --> J
    AI -- No --> AJ[Build final suite]
    AC -- No --> AJ

    AJ --> AK[Keep compliant artifact-backed reproducible official distance failures]
    AK --> AL[Allow mission outcomes completed or not_completed; reject unknown]
    AL --> AM[Sort by robust rank key]
    AM --> AN[Filter by obstacle distance and trajectory DTW]
    AN --> AO[Save final tree, history, and three separate progress plots]
    AO --> AP[Copy selected suite to best_ranked_failed_tests]
    AP --> AQ[CLI exports generated_tests using the same run id]
